I love this bar! Friday night karaoke is my jam and I go at least twice a month! I cannot get enough. The bar staff is the best and the KJ is awesome! If you treat them right, they will treat you right! They also have "beer" pong set up and giant jenga if you're looking to play some games and drink. Right across the street there are two restaurants open late (hot dog/burger joint and Mexican restaurant), which is very convenient! They close at 2, but if you want to stay out later there's a bar next door that's open later.
Jenga and beer pong!

We went after a Cubs game for some drinks and food. Not too busy which I found strange as a lot of people were walking past. Sausages are good but not the best I've ever had. We tried to order a pitcher of beer but was told they didn't have pitchers (it was listed on the menu) only to have the water delivered in a beer pitcher... Instead we we're practically forced to order this obnoxiously tall dispenser of which the name elludes me at the moment. May go back but would probably try a different place on the street next time.
Great place after a game!

Clemson bar in Chicago? Automatic 5 stars. Bar tender was a cool dude. Was pretty knowledgeable about beers as well. Made for a good time. the Clemson flags all over the walls were just icing on the cake.

What a neat bar!!!! We were in Chicago for a cheer competition and made a point to see Wrigley field. It was so busy because there was a Cubs game that day. We stuck out like a sore thumb being the only people not wearing Cubs gear but that's ok lol. We decided to stop in for a beer. The guy at the door was really nice. The bartenders were attentive. This is definitely a place to stop at for a genuine Chicago bar visit.

A deal for $1.00 beers was advertised for March 11th. That deal can still be found on their website. The waitress would not honor the posted deal. I don't understand why they wouldn't honor a deal that is on their website. We talked to the manager and he was able to justify the descrepancy, but very reluctantly. I did not feel like he cared a bit about our satisfaction or rectifying the issue. He honored the deal because he was forced to. Beyond that fiasco: it was cold, every member of the staff was rude, and it just was overall not worth even the trip across the street. We live across the street and would rather go to any bar in the area. They are desperate to get people in the doors so they resort to false advertising.
Low key and easy. Sign up for their email list and win a free party.
I think I our group went at the wrong time.

Not coming back!  As a regular of this place, mostly for the free hot dogs, I tried to go when the Cubs were in the World Series.  They were charging $60.00 just to get in!  That's is, I found a new place to go - two doors down, much nicer place and the staff is way nicer.  Goodbye Full Shilling!

One of the best places to party before, during or after the Cubs games.  Great drink and food specials.  Free hot dogs and popcorn.

Came in before a game with my fiancé, bartender was rude, and didn't even ask if we would like to see the menu. I ordered a Bloody Mary and it sucked BIG time! Premade mix and not any garnishing ' s, for $10! Come on part of the fun of a bloody is all the fixings! Not recommended!  #nogo!

First time there headed to a Cubs game, wife and I ordered a bloody Mary only to find out it was a mix from a bottle...if that's what you offer that's ok but give me a pickle at minimum...and of you aren't even going to to do that do NOT charge me $10 per drink if that is ALL you can offer...not to mention that it was by far one of the worst customer experiences we have encountered. This is Chicago and we should have a good taste in our mouth for one of the biggest cities in the country...am I wrong?
The rumored $1 hot dog has gone missing, but every time I am there I find myself sitting at the bar for much longer than expected. Always a good crowd that ropes you in.

This bar is a wrigleyville staple. I'm so sad though they got rid of their tall boy and hot dog deal after cubbies' wins!  They had all the fixings available!  The popcorn is still there and trivia on Tuesdays is a good time.
Love this place!
if you want to go out with no make up on and still have a crazy night with friends this is the place in wrigleyville to do it.  I suggest the table topper.  Free popcorn...
